ous documents of our age” and “the most perfect example of a human approach to the Jewish-Christian problem.”  afunded by Gormann-Thelen  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aChristianity and other religionsxJudaism. 0aJudaismxRelationsxChristianity. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh1 aAltmann, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEmmet, Dorothy M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGormann-Thelen, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendes-Flohr, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendes-Flohr, Paul.1 aRosenstock-Huessy, Eugen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosenstock-Huessy, Eugen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStahmer, Harold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStahmer, Harold.2 aGormann-Thelenefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226728025423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226728025.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles